---
title: Sweet Chilli Cauli, Prawn and Chickpea Red Thai Style Curry with Jasmine Rice and Coriander
description: Looking for a quick and tasty midweek dinner option? Try cooking up our Sweet Chilli Cauli, Prawn and Chickpea Red Thai Style Curry in just 20-25 minutes for a delicious and speedy meal.
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/HF_Y24_R18_W17_UK_QV16702-4_Mainlow-fe23abba.jpg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.co.uk/recipecards/card/65d7188d7597174e16c13df1.pdf
author: HelloFresh
cuisine: Thai
course: main course
nutrition:
  calories: 796 kcal
  fat: 31.5 g
  saturated fat: 20.7 g
  carbohydrates: 98.5 g
  sugar: 16.8 g
  protein: 28.8 g
  fiber: 5.8 g
  sodium: 3.9 g
  serving size: 607
servings: 2
source: https://www.hellofresh.co.uk/recipes/sweet-chilli-cauli-prawn-and-chickpea-red-thai-style-curry-65d7188d7597174e16c13df1
time required: 20 minutes
---

Preheat your #oven{} to 240°C/220°C fan/gas mark 9. Halve any large
@cauliflower florets{300%grams}.

Pop the cauli onto a #baking tray{}. Drizzle with @oil{}, season with
@salt{} and @pepper{}, then toss to coat. Spread them out in a single layer.

When the oven is hot, roast on the top shelf until golden brown and tender,
~{15-18%minutes}.

Meanwhile, boil a half-full #kettle{}. Drain and rinse the @chickpeas{1%carton}.

Halve the @lime{1}.

Roughly chop the @coriander{1%bunch}(roughly chopped, stalks and all).

Pour the boiled water into a large #saucepan{} with @salt{0.25%tsp} on high
heat. Add the @jasmine rice{150%grams} and cook for ~{10-12%minutes}.

When the cauli is halfway through cooking, remove from the oven and drizzle
over the @sweet chilli sauce{32%grams}.

Turn to glaze the cauli, then return to the oven for the remaining time.

When the rice has 5 mins remaining, heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a large
saucepan on medium-high heat. Drain the @king prawns{150%grams}.

Once hot, add the prawns and stir-fry for ~{2-3%minutes}.

Stir in the @red Thai style paste{50%grams} and @Thai style spice mix{1%sachet}
(add less if you'd prefer things milder) until fragrant, ~{30%seconds}.

Stir in the @coconut milk{200%milliliters}, chickpeas, @vegetable stock paste{10%grams},
and @sugar{0.5%tsp}. Bring to the boil, then lower the heat and simmer until
thickened, ~{3-4%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash hands and utensils after handling raw prawns. Cook so they're
> opaque in the middle.

When the rice is cooked, drain in a #sieve{} and pop back in the pan. Cover with
a #lid{} and leave to the side until ready to serve.

Remove from the heat and add a squeeze of lime. Taste and season with salt,
pepper or lime juice. Add a splash of @?water{} if you feel it needs it.

When everything's ready, stir the roasted cauli into the sauce.

Share your rice between your #serving bowls{}.

Spoon over the prawn red Thai style curry.

Sprinkle over the coriander and serve with any remaining lime wedges for
squeezing over.

Enjoy!